                <expan><abbr>D</abbr><ex>is</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>anibus</ex></expan> Ingen<supplied reason="lost">uus</supplied><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><lb break="no" n="2"/>nis <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilius</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>v</abbr><ex>ixit</ex></expan> <expan><abbr><supplied reason="lost">a</supplied>n</abbr><ex>nos</ex></expan> LV<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="3"/>Tauri <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilia</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>v</abbr><ex>ixit</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>an</abbr><ex>nos</ex></expan> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><lb break="no" n="4"/>tor Tutor In<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="5"/>Gallic<supplied reason="lost">a</supplied>n<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="6"/><expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilii</ex></expan> et her<supplied reason="lost">edes</supplied><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Bei der Auffindung waren drei aneinanderpassende Fragmente erhalten, von denen zwei inzwischen verschollen sind. Maße und Lesung beziehen sich auf den Zustand bei Auffindung. Zahlreiche Ligaturen.</p>
